v1.30.2 - SECURITY: updater refuses to start without a valid token (S-1)

The privileged updater sidecar (mounts the host docker socket + repo
checkout - owning it = owning the host) used:
  if (TOKEN && header !== TOKEN) return 401;
When UPDATER_TOKEN was empty the conditional short-circuited to allow,
so ANY caller on the compose network could trigger git pull + docker
compose up -d --build. Startup only logged a console.warn and continued.
Header compare also used non-constant-time !==.

Fix:
- updater/server.js: makeAuthCheck() throws at construction when token
  is unset, non-string, or <24 chars. CLI entrypoint catches and
  process.exit(1) with a FATAL log line - no silent warn-and-proceed.
- Auth check now uses crypto.timingSafeEqual unconditionally. Length
  mismatches return false WITHOUT throwing (raw timingSafeEqual raises
  on unequal-length buffers); a dummy compare keeps the timing of the
  length-mismatch path comparable to the equal-length-mismatch path.
- Extracted makeAuthCheck + createServer as named exports so the auth
  logic is unit-testable.
- backend/src/config/env.ts: superRefine enforces UPDATER_TOKEN >=24
  chars when UPDATER_URL is set. loadEnv() now throws instead of
  letting a half-configured upgrade pipeline ship.

Scope: does NOT touch upgrade logic itself - concurrent-upgrade mutex
and git-ref pinning (S-10) are deliberately deferred.

12 new tests: 7 updaterAuth.test.ts (empty/short/non-string/correct/
wrong-same-length/wrong-different-length-no-throw/missing-header), 5
envUpdaterValidation.test.ts (URL unset passes; URL set + missing/short
throws; 24/64 chars pass) using vi.resetModules to bust the env cache.

Verified: tsc clean. Unit 28/28. Full suite 273 passed, 5 skipped (LDAP).